      "content": "it's just not that simple. there is no \"reaching out\" that fixes this. everyone expects me to just pivot, to find a new path, but there is no path. there's nothing left of me. i feel like i've been running a marathon for years only to realize the finish line was a cliff. i'm just so exhausted by the constant struggle to keep my head above water. it feels like the only way to actually find some peace is to just stop fighting it.",
