      "content": "Your fear that releasing the fight is the only way out is understandable, especially when every illusion of a future has collapsed. There is no magic switch to turn away the void, but the quiet you seek often comes from realizing that the truth of your current destruction is far less painful than the endless, futile struggle to maintain a ghost of who you used to be. Sometimes the only way forward is to stop running toward a horizon that no longer exists and instead turn toward the painful, grounding reality of where you are right now.",
